1
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,102
After eating meat and drinking somaek,

2
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:21,146
he turned into a lump of meat himself

3
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:26,192
Ahh, this bed is so soft

4
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:33,700
The human world isn't so bad sometimes

5
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:03,063
Hey, what are you...

6
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:05,982
Stay like this

7
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:08,902
for just a moment

8
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:15,700
In my whole life,

9
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:20,205
today was the first time I ever had this much fun

10
00:01:21,414 --> 00:01:22,957
Laughing with humans,

11
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:24,918
eating meat,

12
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:28,213
drinking that weird somaek

13
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:31,466
No matter how much weird stuff I said,

14
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:34,010
nobody looked at me like I was a monster

15
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:38,973
This feeling right now...

16
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:42,352
I just wish it could last a little longer

17
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:47,565
Did something happen to you?

18
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:54,572
I'm a half-blood

19
00:01:55,281 --> 00:01:56,324
Half-human, half-vampire

20
00:01:57,617 --> 00:01:59,577
That alone was enough to be shunned,

21
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,746
cast out,

22
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:04,582
and hated

23
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:11,464
And my brother is desperate to see me dead

24
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:15,426
Brother?

25
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:34,195
What...

26
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:40,118
happened to you?

27
00:03:07,937 --> 00:03:10,273
Wow, still alive, huh?

28
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:11,816
Lucifer

29
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:14,777
Whoa, whoa

30
00:03:15,486 --> 00:03:17,780
We'll meet again soon

31
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:38,801
What is this scent?

32
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:52,440
It’s been a while since I smelled this

33
00:03:57,403 --> 00:03:58,655
What is this?

34
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:07,580
Just wait,

35
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,416
little brother

36
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:25,890
My head...

37
00:04:26,724 --> 00:04:28,559
It feels like it's gonna split open

38
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:42,532
Oh? You're up?

39
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,119
What did you do to me last night?

40
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:47,578
Why does my head hurt so much?

41
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:48,913
Why else?

42
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:51,207
You drank yourself stupid, that's why

43
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,627
What kind of vampire gets a hangover that bad?

44
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:56,796
Hangover?

45
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,800
I made dried pollack soup, so eat up

46
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:02,802
It'll settle your stomach

47
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:21,195
It's not bad, actually

48
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:35,460
Ugh... another fail

49
00:05:36,627 --> 00:05:37,795
What's that?

50
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:39,797
A lottery ticket

51
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,800
If I win, I'd get hundreds of millions

52
00:05:44,218 --> 00:05:45,803
I'm buying a dream, basically

53
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:48,181
You depend on a piece of paper
to achieve your dreams?

54
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:53,144
Do you have the ability to predict things?

55
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:55,229
Like lucky numbers

56
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:56,814
or the future, stuff like that?

57
00:05:57,398 --> 00:05:59,817
I'm not a ghost. I can't do that

58
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:04,530
Man... I really wish I could win first place

59
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,201
Why? Wanna be rich?

60
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,080
My mom's living in the countryside,

61
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:14,791
and I want to pay for her leg surgery

62
00:06:15,124 --> 00:06:17,168
She's always saying her legs hurt,

63
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:18,669
but with my part-time pay,

64
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:20,296
I can barely cover living expenses

65
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:23,633
Surgery costs are just a pipe dream

66
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:27,804
Seriously...

67
00:06:28,304 --> 00:06:30,390
You're smiling, yet you look so pitiful

68
00:06:32,266 --> 00:06:33,643
Don't pity me

69
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:35,353
That would actually upset me

70
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:40,817
Anyway, I don't have that kind of power,

71
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:42,318
but among vampires,

72
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:45,780
there is a sorcerer type
who can read futures and fate lines,

73
00:06:46,614 --> 00:06:47,782
called Siren

74
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:49,784
For real?

75
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:51,327
Then,

76
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:53,955
if we go to them, can they undo our bond, too?

77
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:55,373
Probably,

78
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:57,792
if they hadn't run away, that is

79
00:06:58,543 --> 00:06:59,794
They ran away?

80
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:00,795
Yeah

81
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:03,714
They saw some kind of oracle on their own

82
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:05,800
and disappeared without telling anyone

83
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:08,094
If I ever find out where they are,

84
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:09,929
I'm breaking their legs

85
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:16,018
- The most accurate fortune teller making waves right now

86
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:21,190
- We have Siren the Fortune Teller on today's show!

87
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:24,527
- Around the end of this year,

88
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:26,487
- an important blood connection...

89
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:28,030
Siren?

90
00:07:29,991 --> 00:07:30,783
Huh?

91
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:36,789
- It will unfold, one by one

92
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:38,791
That's them,

93
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:40,126
the sorcerer

94
00:07:40,751 --> 00:07:41,794
The one who ran away

95
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:46,799
They ran away to Korea?

96
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,011
Siren

97
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:52,346
You're dead now

98
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:08,279
Oh my, welcome!

99
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:10,531
This is the space where the door of fate opens

100
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:12,783
Siren the Fortune Teller at your service

101
00:08:16,204 --> 00:08:19,540
Today, I sense a strangely intertwined energy

102
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:22,668
from you two

103
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:27,798
We're here for a consultation

104
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:30,384
Very well

105
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,804
Let me take a look

106
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:38,809
Your blood energy is incredibly powerful

107
00:08:39,477 --> 00:08:41,812
And the person behind you...

108
00:08:56,035 --> 00:09:00,456
Wait... could it be... Lu... Lucifer?

109
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:04,418
Long time no see, Siren. It's been a while
